;;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
;;; RESEARCH: [title of finding]
;;;
;;; PURPOSE: [one sentence — what novel claim this makes]
;;;
;;; BUILDS ON: [which domain/ files provide the grounded facts]
;;; STATUS: [HYPOTHESIS | TESTED | CONFIRMED | PUBLISHED]
;;;
;;; DISTINCTION FROM DOMAIN FILES:
;;; Domain files contain accepted facts with authoritative sources.
;;; Research files contain NOVEL CLAIMS built on those facts.
;;; Every novel claim must:
;;;   1. State what is novel (what has no prior work)
;;;   2. State what domain facts it depends on (traceable)
;;;   3. State what would falsify it (testable)
;;;   4. State the evidence for and against (honest)
;;;
;;; EVIDENCE STANDARD:
;;;   HYPOTHESIS — logically consistent with domain model, not tested
;;;   TESTED     — empirical data collected, analysis performed
;;;   CONFIRMED  — results replicated or independently verified
;;;   PUBLISHED  — submitted to peer review
;;;
;;; SOURCES: Same standard as domain files for cited facts.
;;; Novel claims are marked explicitly as novel.
;;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

